>
  <h2>What a full replacement includes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Tear-off to deck. No "overlay" shortcuts — Texas hot + humid is no climate for a two-layer
      roof.
    </li>
    <li>
      Synthetic underlayment (GAF Deck-Armor) + peel-and-stick ice-and-water shield at valleys and
      penetrations.
    </li>
    <li>New drip edge, new pipe boots, new ridge vents if applicable.</li>
    <li>
      GAF Timberline HDZ architectural shingle, nailed to manufacturer spec (6-nail pattern in
      high-wind zones).
    </li>
    <li>
      50-year non-prorated Golden Pledge manufacturer warranty (requires Master Elite installer — we
      apply for this cert).
    </li>
    <li>
      Forty-photo documentation packet at close — yours to keep, plus a copy for your insurance
      file.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h2>Options worth considering</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Class-4 impact-resistant upgrade</strong> — ~$1,800–$3,200 extra on a typical Woodlands
      home; most TX carriers give a meaningful wind/hail-portion discount. Usually pays back in 3–6 years.
      See <a href="/blog">our Class-4 IR shingle breakdown</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Ridge vent upgrade</strong> — $600–$900; cuts attic temps and extends shingle life. If your
      current roof had turbines, we'll quote both.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Solar-ready deck prep</strong> — if you're planning solar in the next 3 years, we can pre-flash
      key locations.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h2>What the process looks like</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Free inspection + written estimate — same day you call.</li>
    <li>Material selection + color sample drop-off.</li>
    <li>
      HOA ARC submittal (we handle for Bridgeland, Towne Lake, Alden Bridge, Timarron, and others).
    </li>
    <li>Install day — usually one day, two for larger homes. Project manager on-site.</li>
    <li>Final walk-through, magnet sweep of driveway + yard, documentation packet delivered.</li>
  </ol>
</ServiceLayout>
